                    <span>...with regards to COM+ before I read this book. A definite eye-opener! Very well written, explains in a concise manner both the big picture but most importantly IMHO the little details, those little holes that prevent you from fully understanding what is going on, what is happening, when, where and why.<br>I had considerable plain-vanilla-COM experience when I read it, but I believe it can be of immense help even to COM novices (I wish I had read that amazing explanation of COM apartments as a thread affinity issue a couple of years back).<br>This book is so good, I would gladly buy a second copy!!!<br>Thank you, thank you, thank you Tim!!!</span>
                  
